The 16-year-old boy’s body was discovered near the Pampierstad cemetery on Thursday. CAPE TOWN - Police are searching for suspects in connection with the murder of a Northern Cape teenager. It’s believed the 16-year-old boy was strangled with a bicycle chain. The young victim’s body was discovered near the Pampierstad cemetery on Thursday. No arrests have been made yet. Police spokesperson Captain Sergio Kock says, “This happened on 6 September when a passer-by alerted the police. The deceased was found on a ground with a bicycle chain around his neck.” (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)